<title type="html"><![CDATA[Use a level of indirection]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=558&amp;p=4576#p4576"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">ok wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />So how do you sort y values and still have them associated with their coresponding x values after the sort?<br /></div><br />You create a separate array of object numbers, from 0 to n-1, and then sort those. For example, if you're comparing 3 and 5, look up object_y[3] and object_y[5], compare them, and then swap the 3 and the 5 if necessary.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Thu Sep 15, 2005 1:55 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
